🚀 **DevOps & Cloud Quick Notes – GCP + Linux Essentials**

Today I revised some important **GCP IAM** and **Linux administration** commands that every DevOps Engineer should have at their fingertips 👇

🔐 **GCP – Grant Access (IAM)**
➡️ Go to IAM → Grant Access
➡️ Add user email in *New Principal*
➡️ Assign appropriate role (Viewer/Editor/Custom)

🐧 **Linux Commands Cheat Sheet**

👤 **User & Access Management**

* Create user: `adduser somesh`
* Switch user: `su username`
* Exit user: `exit`
* Change password: `passwd`
* Delete user: `userdel username`
* Add user to group: `usermod -aG group user`
* Check groups: `getent group`
* Delete group: `delgroup groupname`

⚠️ Deleting a group does NOT delete users, it only removes group association

🔑 **Root Access**

* Edit sudoers: `vi /etc/sudoers`
* Add: `username ALL=(ALL:ALL) ALL`

📂 **File & Permissions**

* Check permissions: `ls -l`
* Make executable: `chmod +x script.sh`
* Folder size: `du -sh`

📊 **Process Monitoring**

* All processes: `ps -aef`
* User-specific: `ps -u username`
* Java processes: `ps -aef | grep java`
* OOM issues: `ps -aef | grep oom`

📦 **Backup & Archiving**

* Create tar: `tar -cvf backup.tar myfiles`
* Extract tar: `tar -xvf backup.tar`

☁️ **Log Backup to S3 (Basic Flow)**

1. Compress logs using `tar`
2. Upload using AWS CLI:
   `aws s3 cp backup.tar s3://bucket-name/`

📁 **Quick File Creation**
`mkdir myfiles && touch myfiles/{file1.txt,file2.txt}`

🧠 Small commands, BIG impact in real-world troubleshooting & production support!

